<HEADLINE>
<P>
COMMUNITY NEWS: EL SEGUNDO; POLICE RELEASE SKETCH OF RAPE, ROBBERY SUSPECT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JAMES BENNING 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 El Segundo police have released a sketch of an acne-scarred man suspected of 
raping a Danish tourist and robbing three businesses Aug. 21 during a 
late-night crime spree. 
</P>
<P>
 Witnesses and the 20-year-old rape victim provided police with a description 
of the suspect, a black man in his late 20s or early 30s who is 5 feet, 9 
inches tall, with short, dark hair, a light mustache and a gold earring in his 
left ear. 
</P>
<P>
 The woman, who was touring the country with a friend, was dragged from the 
Hacienda Hotel at 525 N. Sepulveda Blvd. by a gunman who had just robbed a 
sandwich shop and a copy shop in a mini-mall across the street, said El Segundo 
Police Sgt. Glenn Coles.  
</P>
<P>
 The suspect, armed with a semiautomatic handgun, entered the hotel about 12:40 
a.m., demanded money, and ordered hotel employees and patrons to lie on the 
floor. He collected $700 and dragged the woman out a back door. 
</P>
<P>
 The woman was forced into a sedan with a waiting driver and raped twice during 
a two-hour drive through South Bay streets. 
</P>
<P>
 Witnesses described the car as a metallic-painted, four-door sedan with a 
dark, vinyl top and thin whitewall tires with spoke or wire rims. Anyone with 
information may call the El Segundo Police Department at (310) 322-9114, Ext. 
261. JAMES BENNING 
</P>
