<HEADLINE>
<P>
NEIGHBORHOOD EATERY; NEW IDENTITY, SAME SOUL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By MICHAEL KRIKORIAN 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 "I was on the outside looking in," says Bill McCreary, owner of the M & W Soul 
Food Restaurant in Gardena. He literally was. As the owner of a cleaning 
business, twice a month he would be outside what was then named the M & M, 
washing the windows and looking in at people enjoying Mississippi-style 
cooking. 
</P>
<P>
 Then the manager told McCreary that the company was not going to renew the 
lease (there's still an M & M Restaurant in Gardena, though, and other branches 
in Carson, Inglewood and South-Central Los Angeles). McCreary stepped in and 
took the place over. Now McCreary, who used to get $25 a month to clean the 
place, is signing the paychecks. 
</P>
<P>
 Renamed M & W (the W representing McCreary's late partner, Ralph Williams), 
the restaurant opened in May with new booths, paint and lighting. However, 
customers of the old M & M will be glad to know little has changed in terms of 
personnel. Chef Joan Martin, for instance, started at the original M & M at 
95th Street and Avalon Boulevard 18 years ago. The most popular item here is 
the short rib dinner ($9.99), beef short ribs baked for 2 1/2 hours and awash 
in gravy. Diners can select any three from a list of 13 side dishes; a popular 
choice is dressing, macaroni and cheese and candied yams.  
</P>
<P>
 Fried chicken ($6.99) is available three ways: all white meat, all dark, or 
mixed ($1 extra). Another favorite is the fried catfish and red snapper 
($9.99), which can be ordered baked or broiled. 
</P>
<P>
 To celebrate its reopening, the restaurant will be open for 24 hours on Sept. 
9, 10 and 11. 
</P>
<P>
 * M & W is at 2222 Rosecrans Ave., Gardena. (310) 323-0417. Open Sunday 
through Thursday 7 a.m. to 9 p.m., Friday and Saturday 7 a.m. to 10 p.m. 
MICHAEL KRIKORIAN 
</P>
</TEXT>
