<P>
ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: FULLERTON; APPLICANTS SOUGHT FOR 5 PANEL OPENINGS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By MIMI KO 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Applicants are being sought to fill five vacancies on the Central Fullerton 
Redevelopment Project Area Committee. 
</P>
<P>
 The committee reviews proposed projects in the downtown commercial belt along 
Harbor Boulevard from Orangethorpe Avenue to Brea Boulevard and its surrounding 
residential areas. It also makes recommendations to the City Council on 
projects in that central redevelopment area. Those interested in becoming a 
member of the committee must live, work, own property or a business in the 
project area, city officials said. 
</P>
<P>
 Applications are available at City Hall, 303 W. Commonwealth Ave. They must be 
returned by Sept. 12 at 5 p.m. 
</P>
<P>
 For more information, call (714) 738-6311.MIMI KO 
</P>
