<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: ASSISTANCE LEAGUE VOLUNTEERS TO MEET 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By FRANK MESSINA 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Volunteers for the Assistance League of Saddleback Valley, a broad-based 
community support group, will meet Sept. 7. 
</P>
<P>
 The organization takes on a wide range of needs from social work to library 
fund-raising drives in the South County area and is looking for people who can 
volunteer. 
</P>
<P>
 The meeting will take place at the Mission Viejo Country Club, 26200 Country 
Club Drive, at 9:30 a.m. 
</P>
<P>
 Assistance league members are focusing much of their energy toward the 
Operation School Bell project, which purchases and distributes clothing to 
children in the Saddleback Valley Unified School District and the Capistrano 
Unified School District. 
</P>
<P>
 Children who need clothing are referred to the program by administrators and 
social workers in the two school districts.  
</P>
<P>
 The organization also runs a senior meals program that delivered 980 meals to 
elderly persons last year. 
</P>
<P>
 The league's latest project is a push to help at the Mission Viejo and Lake 
Forest library branches. Volunteers mend worn and broken covers, and shelve and 
label books.FRANK MESSINA 
</P>
</TEXT>
