 Fitzgerald said the detail included detectives and others from offices 
throughout the county, but deputies on regular patrol duties were not diverted. 
</P>
<P>
 The gunman, who wore a ski mask, attacked the 17- and 19-year-old clerks after 
taking about $100 from the cash register at a yogurt shop Monday night in 
Camarillo, deputies said. GREG RIPPEE 
