ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: COUNTYWIDE; VOLUNTEERS SOUGHT TO VISIT TERMINALLY ILL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By ALAN EYERLY 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The Kaiser Permanente Hospice program in Orange County is recruiting 
volunteers to visit terminally ill patients in their homes.Volunteers must be 
21 or older and able to work two to four hours per week. 
</P>
<P>
 The program's purpose is to help "make each day as comfortable and meaningful 
as possible" for the patients, said Jan Bennett, who coordinates volunteer 
efforts in Orange County and south Los Angeles County. 
</P>
<P>
 A 32-hour training program for new volunteers will begin in mid-October.  
</P>
<P>
 Information is available from Bennett at (310) 807-6625.ALAN EYERLY 
