<HEADLINE>
<P>
FINAL NFL DRAFT PICK MOORE IS GETTING THE LAST LAUGH AS STARTER WITH PATRIOTS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Tuesday was a good day for Marty Moore, the last pick in this year's NFL 
draft. 
</P>
<P>
 Moore, the 222nd and final selection, will start at right inside linebacker 
for the New England Patriots in Sunday's regular-season opener in Miami. 
</P>
<P>
 He will replace veteran Todd Collins, who has an injured knee. 
</P>
<P>
 Moore, a 6-foot-1, 242-pounder from Kentucky, was dubbed the 19th "Mr. 
Irrelevant" after becoming the last player selected, and was the guest of honor 
at a weeklong festival in Southern California before training camp. 
</P>
<P>
 "My objective was just to make the team," Moore said. "I did that, then an 
unfortunate thing happened, so I'm going to get my chance to start the opener. 
</P>
