COMMUNITY NEWS: HOLLYWOOD; RESERVOIR REOPENING DELAYED FOR TREATMENT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The Hollywood Reservoir will remain closed until Saturday for chlorine 
treatment to remove warm weather bacteria growth. 
</P>
<P>
 The popular recreation area, closed since Monday, was due to reopen Wednesday. 
The postponement was blamed on a delay in the delivery of additives that are 
pumped directly into the water, the Department of Water and Power said. The 
operation does not affect drinking water. 
</P>
<P>
 Customers with questions can contact the DWP water quality help line at (213) 
367-3182. 
</P>
