<HEADLINE>
<P>
BRIEFLY: INTERNATIONAL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Argentina Announces Sweeping Privatization Plan: The government, tightening 
its public finances to shore up what it calls its "economic miracle," said it 
will sell off all major concerns still in the hands of the state within 16 
months. By the end of 1995, all airports, the national post office, the mint 
and the nation's biggest petrochemicals plant will be sold off to private 
ownership, Economy Minister Domingo Cavallo told the annual meeting of the 
country's top bankers. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Column; Brief 
</P>
</TYPE>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> LA090194-0217 </DOCNO>
