<TEXT>
<P>
 Litton Reports $59-Million Loss: The defense contractor said the loss amounted 
to $1.29 a share for its fourth quarter ended July 31.It cited previously 
announced charges for settlement of a federal whistle-blower lawsuit and debt 
retirement. The company earned $45.6 million, or $1.09 a share, in the same 
period a year ago. In July, Litton Industries Inc. announced it had agreed to 
pay $82 million to settle a lawsuit filed by a former employee who accused the 
company of cheating the Pentagon through questionable bookkeeping. 
</P>
