<P>
 United Names Marketing Guru to Head Shuttle Service: The executive will lead 
the carrier's short-haul shuttle into the battle with Southwest Airlines for 
West Coast passengers.Alan B. (Sky) Magary, Shuttle by United's new president, 
had more than 20 years' experience as a marketing executive with Pan Am, 
Republic Airlines and Northwest Airlines. United launches its short-haul 
budget-fare carrier on Oct. 1 with an initial schedule of 184 daily flights in 
eight West Coast markets. The shuttle is a product of the new employee-owned 
UAL Corp., in which the workers surrendered billions of dollars' worth of wages 
and benefits in the hope of making the company more competitive. 
