<TEXT>
<P>
 Philip Morris Plans $6-Billion Stock Buyback: Philip Morris Cos. took major 
steps to strengthen its stock price. It raised the shareholder dividend nearly 
20% and pledged $6 billion to buying back stock over the next three years. The 
moves, authorized by the board of directors, come as the consumer product 
powerhouse known for Marlboro cigarettes, Miller beers and Jell-O desserts is 
under pressure from large investors to boost the value of their holdings. 
</P>
