<P>
 GM to Expand 'Value Pricing' in California: General Motors Corp., aiming to 
wrest market share from Asian competitors, said it will extend its "value 
pricing" strategy in California to 70 models from 46. Selling equipped cars and 
trucks at preset prices without rebates has been paying off for the largest 
U.S. auto maker, GM marketing officials said. The company began the pricing 
strategy in California about a year ago, and some of its car divisions have 
been expanding the program nationwide. 
