<HEADLINE>
<P>
BRIEFLY: TECHNOLOGY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 AT&T Withdraws From Video Game Market: AT&T Corp.'s consumer products unit, in 
an abrupt reversal, said it was canceling plans to manufacture a modem that 
would have allowed users in different locations to play video games with each 
other over phone lines. The device would have been used in conjunction with the 
Sega Genesis and 3DO game machines. In a statement, the AT&T unit said it was 
refocusing its efforts on digital wireless telephones for homes and small 
businesses and globalization of its telephone products, because those areas 
have better profit potential than video game players and peripheral products. 
</P>
</TEXT>
