<P>
GRAPHIX ZONE POSTS LOSS FOR FISCAL YEAR 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The Graphix Zone, a multimedia and CD-ROM company, reported a loss of 
$576,393, or 47 cents a share, for its fiscal year ended June 30.That 
contrasted with a profit of $14,793, or 1 cent a share, for the 11-month period 
ended June 30, 1993. Revenue increased 24% to $2.1 million from $1.7 million.  
</P>
<P>
 The company posted a fourth-quarter loss of $406,452, or 28 cents a share, 
compared to a loss of $49,282, or 2 cents a share, for the like period last 
year. Three-month revenue was up 56% to $840,045 from $537,861. 
</P>
