<HEADLINE>
<P>
BRIEFCASE: REAL ESTATE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
Compiled by Debora Vrana, Times staff writer 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Apartment Sales: Sales of Orange County apartment buildings during the first 
six months of this year remained strong, according to a report filed by CB 
Commercial Real Estate Group Inc. An estimated 39 apartment buildings of more 
than 20 units changed hands during the first half, compared to 24 buildings 
sold during the same period of 1993. 
</P>
<P>
 There are 1,700 apartment buildings of more than 20 units in Orange County, 
the report said. 
</P>
<P>
 The average cost for each unit was down $1,000 from the previous year, a sign 
of stabilization given the $8,000 falloff in prices that occurred between 1992 
and 1993, the study found. 
</P>
<P>
 "We're definitely seeing a comeback to this market and a real run to quality 
projects," said Ray Eldridge, apartment broker at CB Commercial in Laguna 
Hills. 
</P>
</TEXT>
