<P>
BOBBITT IS JAILED FOR BATTERING EX-FIANCEE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 John Wayne Bobbitt was convicted Wednesday of misdemeanor domestic battery 
against his former fiancee by a judge who said Bobbitt has an "attitude 
problem." 
</P>
<P>
 Justice of the Peace William Jansen sentenced Bobbitt to 60 days in jail, then 
suspended 45 days of the sentence.Bobbitt was led from the courtroom in 
handcuffs to begin serving his sentence immediately. 
</P>
<P>
 Bobbitt also was sentenced to six months probation and ordered to attend 
impulse control and Alcoholics Anonymous meetings. 
</P>
<P>
 "I firmly believe you have an attitude problem," Jansen told Bobbitt. "Your 
attitude problem is caused by your drinking." 
</P>
<P>
 Bobbitt, 27, was charged with striking Kristina Elliott, 21, a former exotic 
dancer he met while in Las Vegas on a publicity tour. 
</P>
<P>
 He faces another trial Sept. 26 on a second domestic battery charge involving 
Elliott. In that case, prosecutors say, he slammed Elliott against a wall 
during an argument May 6. 
</P>
<P>
 Bobbitt became famous in June, 1993, when his wife, Lorena, sliced off his 
penis while he slept in their Virginia home. She said she did it because 
Bobbitt had sexually assaulted her. 
</P>
<P>
 Bobbitt's penis was reattached surgically and he was acquitted of marital 
sexual abuse in November. A jury in January found Lorena Bobbitt innocent by 
reason of insanity of mutilating her husband. The couple's divorce is pending. 
</P>
<P>
 On Wednesday, Bobbitt appealed for leniency, saying all the facts did not come 
out at the two-day trial. 
</P>
