<HEADLINE>
<P>
BASEBALL STRIKE: DEVELOPMENTS FROM DAY 20 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 * Games lost: 14. 
</P>
<P>
 * Total games lost: 260. 
</P>
<P>
 * Games remaining: 409. 
</P>
<P>
 * Total income lost by players: $88.3 million. 
</P>
<P>
 * Estimated revenue lost by owners: $170 million. 
</P>
<P>
 * Key development: Key development: Federal mediators met separately with each 
side but didn't call for another bargaining session. 
</P>
<P>
 * In quotes: "He's a prisoner of his own rhetoric." 
</P>
<P>
 -- Donald Fehr union head on management negotiator Richard Ravitch 
</P>
