<HEADLINE>
<P>
LOCAL NOTES: LENAERTS MAKING STRIDES TOWARD RECOVERY, FAMILY SAYS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The mother of La Quinta football player Aron Lenaerts, who lapsed into a coma 
last week during practice, says her son has begun walking and appears on the 
road to a full recovery. 
</P>
<P>
 "I think he's improving every hour," said Bonnie Lenaerts."He's not hooked to 
any IVs or machines; the only thing (doctors) have to give him is some Tylenol 
for a headache, and it's like a regular headache. Every day he's more alert for 
longer periods of time." 
</P>
<P>
 Lenaerts collapsed on Friday during a contact drill and came out of a coma 
Saturday at UCI Medical Center; he began walking Tuesday afternoon, his mother 
said. 
</P>
<P>
 * 
</P>
<P>
 Kim Brown was named Saddleback College's softball coach on Wednesday. Most 
recently an assistant at Capistrano Valley Christian, Brown coached Flagstaff 
(Ariz.) High for two years and also directed a junior club team. 
</P>
<P>
 As a player, she helped Central Arizona College to consecutive National Junior 
College Athletic Assn. championships as its shortstop and cleanup hitter. 
</P>
<P>
 She replaces Jack Robinson, who left after three years with a 68-49 record. 
</P>
</TEXT>
