<HEADLINE>
<P>
BEHIND THE SCENES: FOR WOMEN OF COLOR 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The "Beauty Makeover Secrets for Asian and Hispanic Coloring Workshop" at 
Rancho Santiago Community College in Santa Ana recently attracted a dozen 
women. 
</P>
<P>
 Taught by Betty Nethery, a color and image consultant with Uniquely You in 
Lake Forest, the workshop helped women of color identify the uniqueness of 
their skin tones and facial features.Nethery, a former model and makeup artist, 
told participants to take an honest look at their appearance and invest time to 
look their best. 
</P>
<P>
 Other points made during the 3 1/2-hour program were: 
</P>
<P>
 * Experiment with custom-mixed foundations because skin with golden, yellow, 
gray or green undertones is difficult to match with off-the-shelf foundations. 
</P>
<P>
 * Use eye makeup to contour a flat eyelid shape if you want the illusion of a 
fuller lid, and use blush and foundation to create the look of high cheekbones, 
if so desired. 
</P>
<P>
 * Dark eyes and dark hair look best with makeup in bright tones such as pinks, 
fuchsias, reds and burgundies. Avoid warm, dull or earth tones. 
</P>
<P>
 Another workshop is scheduled for Sept. 29 at Orange Coast College in Costa 
Mesa. The cost is $29. Call (714) 432-5880 for information. 
</P>
</TEXT>
