<HEADLINE>
<P>
LIBERATING THE LEGS; WHEN BARE GAMS WON'T DO, SHEER HOSE AND SUBTLE SOCKS STEP 
IN 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By KATHY BRYANT, SPECIAL TO THE TIMES 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 In olden days, a glimpse of stocking may have been shocking, but today wearing 
no stockings with high heels is the real shocker. 
</P>
<P>
 "At the recent Richard Tyler fall fashion show sponsored by Nordstrom, the 
models wore three-inch and four-inch high heels with no hose," said Mary Dell 
Barkouras, a Newport Beach fashion consultant. "We've seen it in Europe for 
years, but now it's coming here." 
</P>
<P>
 Considering women have been wearing dark hosiery for years, this au natural 
look takes some getting used to. 
</P>
<P>
 The coordinated look of black dress, black hose and black shoes created an 
unbroken line from torso to toe, not to mention that dark hose give the 
illusion of thinner legs. Now, designers want to liberate the leg with either 
no hose or hosiery in natural colors. 
</P>
<P>
 "Only a few women can get away with this look, in my opinion," Dell Barkouras 
says. "It looks best with tanned legs, but we're not supposed to get tans, (so) 
a light-colored hose is needed."  
</P>
<P>
 "The nude leg is certainly a fashion option," said Carol Horowitz, general 
manager of Neiman-Marcus, Fashion Island Newport Beach. "The hosiery to wear 
for the look is ultra sheer. It gives the illusion of no hose." 
</P>
<P>
 For fall, Donna Karan, the largest proponent of black legs, has come out with 
a second-skin hose in Lycra 3-D. 
</P>
<P>
 Karan's and other designers' nude hose colors are designed in many shades to 
wear as a summer tans fade. 
</P>
<P>
 Karan's lightweight hosiery can be mixed with linen to add subtle color and 
texture. 
</P>
<P>
 Socks, too, are adopting the subtle look with heathered colors and mild 
textures for weekend wear. 
</P>
<P>
 "Socks look good worn above the knee and below it," Horowitz says. "The trendy 
look of above-the-knee socks and short skirts can succeed only on those who 
don't mind showing their thighs. Knee socks will also come in the natural 
shades and in outrageous ones like Gianni Versace's shiny silver ones for 
evening wear." 
</P>
</TEXT>
