<DOC>
<DOCNO> LA090194-0370 </DOCNO>
<DOCID> 075253 </DOCID>
<SOURCE>
<P>
 Los Angeles Times 
</P>
</SOURCE>
<DATE>
<P>
September 1, 1994, Thursday, Orange County Edition 
</P>
</DATE>
<SECTION>
<P>
Sports; Part C; Page 20; Column 1; Sports Desk 
</P>
</SECTION>
<LENGTH>
<P>
325 words 
</P>
</LENGTH>
<HEADLINE>
<P>
PREP FOOTBALL '94 / GARDEN GROVE LEAGUE; BOLSA GRANDE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 1993 RECORDS 
</P>
<P>
 OVERALL: 3-7 
</P>
<P>
 LEAGUE: 2-5 
</P>
<P>
 * 
</P>
<P>
 COACH: Earl Graves 
</P>
<P>
 RECORD AT SCHOOL: 0-0 
</P>
<P>
 * 
</P>
<P>
 RETURNING STARTERS 
</P>
<P>
 OFF: 3 
</P>
<P>
 DEF: 2 04,26,05,05,05 TOP RETURNERS OFF DEF YR Yop Jun, 5-10, 194 G DE Sr. 
David Price, 6-2, 167 QB S Sr. David Ross, 5-9, 150 WR CB Sr. Eric Shaner, 6-0, 
184 TE LB Sr. Paul Sharp, 5-10, 148 WR CB Sr. Hae Sung, 5-11, 214 FB LB Sr. 
Danny Thompson, 6-0, 172 RB S Sr. * 04,27,05,05,05 TOP NEWCOMERS OFF DEF YR 
Mike Dalagleish, 6-3, 177 WR S Jr. Dan Hendrix, 5-10, 155 G DE Jr. Thanh 
Nguyen, 5-10, 170 RB LB Jr. OUTLOOK 
</P>
<P>
 It's been five years since Bolsa Grande won more than three games in a season 
and eight years and four coaches since the Matadors won a Garden Grove League 
title. Graves replaces Gary Stephens, who compiled a 4-16 record in two 
seasons. With only five starters returning from last year's team, Bolsa 
Grande's luck doesn't figure to change much. Two-way senior starters Sung, 
Price, Shaner and Jun should give Bolsa Grande some leadership and stability, 
but it probably won't be enough to challenge for a playoff spot. Once again, 
depth will be a problem for the Matadors, who return 15 lettermen. However, 
most of the starters probably will have to play on both sides of the line of 
scrimmage. Bolsa Grande's biggest loss is Brian Baughman, who threw 20 
touchdown passes and netted 2,266 yards, the most of any quarterback in the 
county last year. Price will be given the task of replacing Baughman. Also gone 
is Baughman's favorite wide receiver, Love Jefferson, who caught 36 passes for 
571 yards and eight touchdowns. 
</P>
<P>
 SCHEDULE 
</P>
<P>
 September 9 at Laguna Beach; 15 vs. Whittier Christian; 23 vs. Whittier La 
Serna; 29 vs. Garden Grove. 
</P>
