Mario Carbajal, 6-1, 245 OT DT Jr. Jose Palacios, 5-8, 155 RB DB So. Tom 
Sokanthong, 5-5, 145 RB DB Sr. Octavio Villa, 5-10, 160 QB DB So. OUTLOOK 
</P>
<P>
 Haley could have one of the more difficult coaching jobs in the county, 
rebuilding a winless team that returns only three starters. But Haley helped 
turn around a dreadful Orange program a few years back. In 18 years of 
coaching, he has never had a losing season. In Cortez, Haley has one of the 
league's better athletes. Cortez will move from quarterback to fullback. "I'm 
afraid his productivity would go down if we had him at safety and quarterback," 
Haley said. "If I put Christian at fullback, I know he's going to scratch and 
claw for at least three or four yards. He knows where the hole is going to be. 
And we won't lose much with Octavio, who's more of a pure passer than 
Christian." Haley is also excited about Callari, who didn't play last year. 
"He's a man's man." SCHEDULE 
</P>
