</SECTION>
<LENGTH>
<P>
108 words 
</P>
</LENGTH>
<HEADLINE>
<P>
CITY HALL JOURNAL: LONG BEACH; ARTHUR M. LEW NAMED TO SUPERIOR COURT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Long Beach Municipal Judge Arthur M. Lew has been appointed to the Los Angeles 
County Superior Court by Gov. Pete Wilson. 
</P>
<P>
 Lew, who has been a municipal judge since 1991, will succeed Judge Keith G. 
Wisot, who retired. 
</P>
<P>
 Before being appointed to Municipal Court, Lew, 48, was a deputy district 
attorney from 1984 to 1991. He was a deputy public defender from 1979 to 1984. 
</P>
<P>
 Lew, a Torrance resident, is a member of the California Judges Assn., the Long 
Beach Bar Assn., and the California Chinese Lawyers Assn. He earned a law 
degree from Southwestern School of Law in Los Angeles in 1975 and a bachelor's 
degree from Cal State L.A. in 1970. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Column 
</P>
</TYPE>
</DOC>
