COMMUNITY NEWS: COMPTON; NAT KING COLE STAMP TO BE UNVEILED FRIDAY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The new Nat King Cole commemorative stamp will be unveiled at 10 a.m. Friday 
at Compton Community College, 1111 E. Artesia Blvd. 
</P>
<P>
 On hand will be a daughter of the late crooner, Casey, along with her 
godfather, Sen. Ralph C. Dills (D-El Segundo). The senator's friendship with 
Cole "goes way back," said Tim Mock, Dills' campaign coordinator. Dills, who is 
running for reelection, will give the keynote speech at the ceremony. 
</P>
<P>
 The Postal Service will also unveil a stamp honoring singer Ethel Waters. 
</P>
<P>
 The Dozier Singers gospel group and Group Therapy band will perform. 
