<P>
COMMUNITY NEWS: CERRITOS; PRINCE CHARLES TO ATTEND 'HENRY VI' PERFORMANCE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JOHN CANALIS 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Prince Charles is coming to Cerritos on Nov. 2. 
</P>
<P>
 The Prince of Wales is scheduled to attend the Royal Shakespeare Company 
production of "Henry VI: The Battle for the Throne" at the Cerritos Center for 
the Performing Arts, said John Houlton, British vice consul of information. 
</P>
<P>
 The prince will be in Southern California from Oct. 31 to Nov. 4. He is 
scheduled to meet Los Angeles city officials, attend charity events and tour 
inner-city restoration projects, Houlton said. 
</P>
<P>
 The Royal Shakespeare Company production runs Nov. 1-6 at the performing arts 
center, but the Nov. 2 performance will be by invitation only. Prince Charles 
is president of the Royal Shakespeare Company. JOHN CANALIS 
